<$fill $name="body">

!! `<$action-diffsync>` widget

Action widget that performs comparison and apply operations.

!!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Description |
|`op` |`"compare"` |Operation: `compare`, `apply`, `apply-to-source`, or `clear` |
|`source` |`""` |Title of the source tiddler |
|`target` |`""` |Title of the target tiddler |

!!! Operations

; compare
: Runs field-level comparison between source and target. Stores the result JSON in `$:/temp/diffsync/result` and clears any previous selection state tiddlers. Requires both `source` and `target` to be non-empty.
; apply
: Reads the current comparison result and per-field/per-hunk selection states. For each field with selections, computes the merged value and writes it to the ''target'' tiddler. Multiline fields use `reconstructText`; single-line fields use the selected value directly.
; apply-to-source
: Same as `apply` but writes to the ''source'' tiddler. For multiline fields, the source/target are swapped in the reconstruction and unselected hunks are inverted to produce the correct result.
; clear
: Deletes `$:/temp/diffsync/result` and all `$:/state/diffsync/field/*` tiddlers.

!!! Usage example

```
<$button>
  <$action-diffsync op="compare" source="TiddlerA" target="TiddlerB"/>
  Compare
</$button>
```

!! Library: diff-hunks.js

Exported functions from `$:/plugins/rimir/diffsync/diff-hunks.js` (module-type: library):

|!Function |!Signature |!Description |
|`lineDiff` |`(sourceText, targetText)` |Returns raw diff-match-patch line-level diffs as `[type, text]` tuples |
|`computeHunks` |`(sourceText, targetText, contextLines?)` |Computes hunks with context (default 3 lines). Returns `[{id, lines}]` |
|`reconstructText` |`(sourceText, targetText, hunks, selections)` |Rebuilds text from hunks + selection map `{hunkId: "source"}` |
|`compareFields` |`(wiki, sourceTitle, targetTitle, contextLines?)` |Full field-level comparison. Returns array of field diff entries |
|`isMultiline` |`(val)` |Returns `true` if the string contains `\n` |

!! Hunk data format

Each hunk object:

```json
{
  "id": 0,
  "lines": [
    {"type": "equal",  "text": "unchanged line\n"},
    {"type": "delete", "text": "removed from source\n"},
    {"type": "insert", "text": "added in target\n"},
    {"type": "equal",  "text": "unchanged line\n"}
  ]
}
```

* `id` -- integer, sequential starting at 0
* `lines[].type` -- `"equal"`, `"delete"` (source-only), or `"insert"` (target-only)
* `lines[].text` -- the line content including its trailing newline

!! Field diff data format

Each entry in the comparison result array:

```json
{
  "field": "text",
  "sourceVal": "source field value",
  "targetVal": "target field value",
  "sourceOnly": false,
  "targetOnly": false,
  "isMultiline": true,
  "hunks": [...]
}
```

* `field` -- field name (never `"title"`)
* `sourceVal` / `targetVal` -- stringified values, or `undefined` if the field is absent
* `sourceOnly` / `targetOnly` -- `true` when the field exists in only one tiddler
* `isMultiline` -- `true` if either value contains `\n`
* `hunks` -- only present when `isMultiline` is true; array of hunk objects

!! State tiddler layout

|!Tiddler pattern |!Content |
|`$:/state/diffsync/source` |Selected source tiddler title |
|`$:/state/diffsync/target` |Selected target tiddler title |
|`$:/state/diffsync/field/<fieldName>` |`"source"` = use source value; empty/absent = use target value |
|`$:/state/diffsync/field/<fieldName>/hunk/<id>` |`"source"` = use source lines for this hunk; empty/absent = use target lines |
|`$:/temp/diffsync/result` |JSON comparison result (type `application/json`); also has `source` and `target` fields |

!! Config tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/diffsync/context-lines` |`3` |Number of unchanged lines shown before and after each hunk |

</$fill>
</$transclude>
